* Editor's note: This live event will be broadcast live on eNCA.com and is expected to start at 4.30pm.JOHANNESBURG - A memorial service will be held for journalist and senior SABC radio producer, Suna Venter. Her body was discovered in her Johannesburg flat on Thursday morning.She died of a heart condition, thought to be brought on by trauma and prolonged stress.READ: One of SABC8 journalists found dead in flatThe 32-year-old endured intimidation, threats and assaults, as she fought to report freely and accurately at the public broadcaster.Venter was part of a group of eight SABC journalists, who were fired for objecting to former COO Hlaudi Motsoeneng's policies.The service will be held at the SABC's offices in Auckland Park.eNCA